the bad plus events at stanford the bad plus facebook twitter email print add to calendar for the past ten years the bad plus bassist reid anderson pianist and sjw alum ethan iverson and drummer david king have broken down the walls of jazz convention and created an uncompromising body of work largely original and based on what they call their personal brand of avant garde populism though firmly rooted in the acoustic jazz piano trio tradition their stylistic appetite is huge encompassing pop rock country electronic and classical idioms the bad plus are a reminder that american jazz hasn t gone to sleep noted the observer music monthly play any of the their albums and their collective sound leaps out of your speakers steps all over your furniture and scares the bejesus out of the cat when tuesday august 2 2011 8 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where dinkelspiel auditorium 471 lagunita dr stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor stanford jazz workshop contact 736 0324 info stanfordjazz org admission tickets $36 general $22 students stanford ticket office 650 725 arts 2787 http tickets stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 279 27995 more info last modified july 26 2011
